<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8 offset-md-2">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                <h2 class="mb-0">Basic Authentication Success</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <h4 class="alert-heading">Authentication Successful!</h4>
                    <p>{{message}}</p>
                </div>
                
                <h4>User Information:</h4>
                <table class="table table-striped">
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <th>User ID:</th>
                            <td>{{user.userId}}</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Username:</th>
                            <td>{{user.username}}</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
                
                <h4 class="mt-4">How Basic Authentication Works:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>The client makes a request to a protected resource.</li>
                    <li>The server responds with a 401 Unauthorized status and includes a WWW-Authenticate header.</li>
                    <li>The browser prompts the user for credentials.</li>
                    <li>The credentials are sent in the Authorization header in base64 encoded format.</li>
                    <li>The server decodes the credentials and validates them.</li>
                    <li>If valid, the server grants access to the protected resource.</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h4 class="mt-4">Security Considerations:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Basic Authentication should only be used over HTTPS to prevent credential theft.</li>
                    <li>Passwords should be securely hashed (not stored in plain text).</li>
                    <li>For production systems, consider more robust authentication mechanisms like JWT or OAuth 2.0.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="card-footer">
                <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Back to Home</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div> 